article.headline: High Point 63, Loyola, Md. 57
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Mike Jefferson led all scorers with a career-high 27 points as High Point defeated Loyola of Maryland 63-57 on Friday. Jefferson completed 6-of-15 from the field and connected on 12-of-15 free throws for High Point (8-5), which had a 30-24 lead at halftime. Loyola (5-4) kept the game close at the beginning of the second half and took a 54-53 lead with 4:35 remaining. High Point then went on a 10-3 run to earn the win. High Point scored 20 points off Loyola turnovers and scored 15 fast-break points. Jefferson was the only Panther to score in double figures. Eugene Harris and Landon Quick each had eight points for High Point. Marquis Sullivan led Loyola with 17 points, Gerald Brown chipped in 12 and Omari Israel had 11.
